default              
defaultI have a concern about any kind of deal that John Kerry produces. On the one hand, as Professor Hollis just said, it is correct that most Palestinians just do not have much faith in their leaders and are too disillusioned to respond much. That does not mean that they have bought in; they might not do anything physical against it for a while. However, is that a peace upon which both Palestinians and Israel can actually build much further, without bringing Gaza—and therefore Hamas—back into the equation? 
default              
